(15, 'Jothi Saldanha', 'Jothi', 'Saldanha', 'Jothi Creative Wellness', 'Jothi is a multi-award-winning Transformational Wellness Coach with over 10 years of experience in community engagement, mental health advocacy, and holistic wellness for individuals, communities, and corporate settings.\r\n\r\nAs a mother of two teenagers, Jothi\'s personal healing journey began nearly 18 years ago with the birth of her first child. This transformative experience resurfaced her own childhood and birthing traumas, inspiring her to take healing seriously—for her own well-being, to break generational cycles of pain, and to nurture her inner child while deepening her relationship with her mother.\r\n\r\nJothi’s superpower lies in holding space for others in real and meaningful ways. Through compassionate inquiry, curiosity, intuitive guidance, and a gentle, loving approach, she creates a safe and affirming environment. She works from a decolonized and culturally sensitive lens, acknowledging intersectional lived experiences and diverse healing pathways.\r\n\r\nJothi is certified in various unique modalities, including Integrative Somatic Trauma Therapy, Sacred Leadership, Neuro-Linguistic Programming, and Quantum Healing. She integrates creative expression, movement, touch, meditation, breathwork, and intuitive tools to support her clients on their healing journeys.\r\n\r\nPassionate about community engagement, Jothi is the visionary behind HERSpace, a hybrid space for women-identifying individuals to experience collective care, healing, and wellness. This space centers the strengths and struggles of racialized communities while uplifting and honoring ancient sacred practices. Jothi believes that reclaiming ancestral wisdom and traditional medicines is key to affirming identity and cultural roots.\r\n\r\nJothi is here to connect deeply, move intentionally, and provide a soft, caring space for you to land.', '[\"115\"]', 'info@jothi.ca', NULL, '$2y$12$uhe5ifRPSJ8/qRFwC9V0seG2OMJtL3r