(51, 51, 'Lauren Best is a Certified Hypnotherapist, Transformation Designer, and the Founder of Possibilities Universe. She helps people break free from perfectionism, self-sabotage, and limiting beliefs by reconnecting with their intuition, celebrating themselves, and embracing their fullest potential.\r\n\r\nLauren’s approach to hypnotherapy is rooted in helping people release the pressure of external expectations and find momentum through self-trust, joy, and experimentation. With a deep understanding of how perfectionism and internalized \'not enoughness\' can hold people back, Lauren uses hypnosis to rewire the subconscious mind, offering clients new pathways toward self-worth, creativity, and freedom.\r\n\r\nHer journey toward becoming a hypnotherapist was shaped by her own experience of navigating environments that didn’t quite fit. With a background in product and furniture design in London and a career in business transformation design in Singapore, Lauren often felt drawn toward doing things differently. This desire to break free from traditional molds eventually led her to create Possibilities Universe — a space designed to inspire self-trust, creative experimentation, and self-celebration.\r\n\r\nLauren’s signature Celebrate Yourself Card Deck was born from this mission, encouraging people to pause, acknowledge their progress, and honour their inner voice. Alongside her private hypnotherapy sessions, she also facilitates group workshops, guided visualizations, and creative experiences that help individuals pursue their most authentic dreams without fear of failure.\r\n\r\nLauren believes the subconscious mind holds the key to unlocking untapped potential. By helping her clients rewrite old narratives, she supports them in overcoming self-doubt, fear of success, and internalized pressure. Her work offers a safe space for people to dream bigger, trust themselves, and celebrate every step of their journey — imperfections and all.', NULL, '[\"115\",\"116\",\"118\",\"374\",\"884\"]', '[\"20\"]', '{\"profile_image\":\"1741651207_1000080125.jpg\",\"media_images\":[]}', NULL, NULL, '2,4,5,7,12,16,63,67,97,106,107,108,122,143,144,145,157,236,242,264,265,266,300,312,322,328,329,330,331,332,333', '1,8,10,29,30,48,66,74,115,143,148,162,163', '[\"4\",\"6\"]', '78', 'America/Vancouver', '[\"Virtual offerings\"]', 0, 0, 0, 'Introduction\r\n\r\nThis Privacy Policy describes how Possibilities Universe (\"we,\" \"us,\" or \"our\") collects, uses, and protects your personal information when you visit our website www.possibilities-universe.com and engage with our services. We are committed to safeguarding your privacy in accordance with the applicable privacy laws in Canada, including the Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act (PIPEDA).\r\n\r\n​\r\n\r\nInformation We Collect\r\n\r\nWe may collect the following types of personal information:\r\n\r\nPersonal Identification Information: Name, email address, phone number, mailing address, and any other information you voluntarily provide when you contact us or register for our services.\r\n\r\nPayment Information: Credit card information and billing address when you make a purchase. This information is processed securely through third-party payment processors.\r\n\r\nUsage Data: Information about how you interact with our website, including IP address, browser type, pages visited, time spent on pages, and other analytical data.\r\n\r\nCookies: We may use cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance your browsing experience and collect information about how you use our website.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nHow We Use Your Information\r\n\r\nWe may use your personal information for the following purposes:\r\n\r\nTo provide and manage our services and products.\r\n\r\nTo process your transactions and send you confirmation and updates.\r\n\r\nTo communicate with you, including responding to inquiries and sending newsletters or promotional materials.\r\n\r\nTo improve our website and services by analyzing user behavior and preferences.\r\n\r\nTo comply with legal obligations and protect our rights.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nDisclosure of Your Information\r\n\r\nWe do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to outside parties without your consent, except as described below:\r\n\r\nService Providers: We may share your information with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating our website, conducting our business, or servicing you, provided that these parties agree to keep this information confidential.\r\n\r\nLegal Compliance: We may disclose your personal information if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities (e.g., a court or a government agency).\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nSecurity of Your Information\r\n\r\nWe implement a variety of security measures to maintain the safety of your personal information when you place an order or enter, submit, or access your personal information. However, no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nThird-Party Websites\r\n\r\nOur website may contain links to third-party websites. We do not control and are not responsible for the content or privacy practices of these websites. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party sites you visit.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nYour Rights\r\n\r\nYou have the right to:\r\n\r\nAccess your personal information and request corrections to inaccuracies.\r\n\r\nWithdraw your consent to the collection, use, or disclosure of your personal information.\r\n\r\nRequest the deletion of your personal information, subject to certain exceptions.\r\n\r\nTo exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the information provided below.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nChanges to This Privacy Policy\r\n\r\nWe may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any updates.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nContact Us\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, or if you wish to exercise your rights regarding your personal information, please contact Lauren by email at hello@lauren-best.com.', 'By purchasing a program, course, service, physical, or digital product, either partially or in full, you agree to the following terms:\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nAgreement\r\n\r\nThese terms outline your agreement between you (the Customer), Lauren Best (the Service Provider), and Possibilities Universe (the Company). Should any questions or concerns arise regarding these policies, please bring them to my attention.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nConfidentiality\r\n\r\nThe Service Provider agrees that the content held at each session remains confidential to create a strong foundation and alliance that will support the Customer in reaching their goals. The Customer is free to share whatever they choose from their sessions with their spouse, family, etc., as this is a powerful way of reinforcing new insights and skills.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nSession Preparation\r\n\r\nAll post-coaching reflections, previous session work, and/or coaching prep sheets must be completed by the Customer 24 hours prior to the next session and submitted via the instructions set by the Service Provider.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nRecording Policy\r\n\r\nWorkshop sessions may be recorded by the Service Provider without being redistributed to the attendees. Failure to attend a live workshop will not guarantee that the Customer will have access to the session recording for later viewing. Private sessions may be recorded upon request by the Customer and will be made available by the Service Provider for download within 14 days after the session for personal viewing only.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nCustomer Responsibility\r\n\r\nThe Customer is 100% r