(69, 69, 'Trace Miller is the founder of Innate Wisdom: Transformational Healing. She is a Certified MindBody Practitioner & Holistic Healing Coach. Trace teaches people with chronic pain and symptoms who are feeling hopeless and unsupported how to achieve long-lasting healing and change. Trace has been coaching people 1:1 with extremely effective results using pain neuroscience, evidence-based pain recovery therapies and mind-body coaching.', 'Innate Wisdom: Transformational Healing for Chronic Pain & Symptoms', '[\"988\"]', '[]', '{\"profile_image\":\"1740931017_Origin-Bio-photo.jpg\"}', 'Trace has been an advocate of holistic health for 20+ years. As a Certified MindBody Practitioner and Holistic Healing Coach, Trace specializes in helping individuals overcome persistent pain and symptoms, especially when conventional treatments that focus solely on the physical aspects haven’t provided relief. Trace addresses the brain-body connection ad guide people to achieve long-lasting relief from their symptoms. Her 1:1 coaching sessions combine education of pain neuroscience (the brain-pain-fear cycle that effects chronic pain/symptoms), the interconnectedness of physical and emotional well-being, mindset empowerment, and mind-body therapies. Trace knows what it is like as she has her own healing journey and offers compassion, accountability, expertise, understanding and support.\r\n\r\nThis work is quite profound for most people because we grew up with a different understanding - if we have pain, there is a physical cause of the pain. This is simply not true.\r\nLooking solely at the physical symptoms is an oversight. Contrary to belief, you can’t understand pain unless you understand how the brain works.\r\nAll pain starts in the brain. All pain is 100% real.\r\n\r\nYour brain can create a cycle of pain due to neural circuits that get activated due to stress and emotions in life situations - this is called Neuro-plastic pain, or Neuro-circuit pain or MindBody Syndrome. Your brain is saying, look, I\'m worried about you, there\'s something wrong, there\'s something amiss.\r\n\r\nWith chronic symptoms, our brain has created a pathway which remembers the pain and keeps you trapped in a vicious cycle. > pain, fear, pain, fear (refer to one of the images).\r\n\r\nFurthermore, research shows, that emotions and stress activate the exact same parts of the brain as does a physical injury. If you’ve ever experienced a broken heart and experienced actually chest pain, that’s exactly what’s going on. And the same thing occurs with chronic pain. Your pain is getting activated from stress.\r\n\r\nSo the pain that occurs due to a fracture is exactly the same as the pain the occurs due to a stressful situation that occurs in your life. They are both very real and can be very severe. However acute pain and injuries heal. Chronic issues too often perpetuate the brain-pain-fear cycle.\r\n\r\nOnce you understand the cause of pain, you are empowered to heal.', NULL, '10,15,17,19,21,120,126,129,167,168,169,170,171,172,173,174,176,177,178,179,181,182,183,185,186,188,190,191,192,193,194', '61,62,63,64,65,66,67,68,69', '[]', '33,34,35,36,37', 'America/Vancouver', NULL, 0, 0, 0, NULL, NULL, '2025-03-02 05:16:20', '2025-03-10 07:54:44', NULL, '{\"every_day\":{\"from\":null,\"to\":null},\"every_monday\":{\"from\":null,\"to\":null},\"every_tuesday\":{\"from\":null,\"to\":null},\"every_wednesday\":{\"from\":null,\"to\":null},\"every_thursday\":{\"from\":null,\"to\":null},\"every_friday\":{\"from\":null,\"to\":null},\"weekends_only_-_every_sat_&_sundays\":{\"from\":null,\"to\":null}}', NULL),
